### Simplicial connections

* **Definition.** Let $\mathcal{E}_\bullet$ be a simplicial vector bundle. Write $\pi_p\colon Y_p\times\Delta^p\to Y_p$. Then a **connection** on $$\overline{\mathcal{E}_p}=\pi_p^*\mathcal{E}_p=\mathcal{E}_p\otimes_{\mathcal{O}_{Y_p}}\mathcal{O}_{Y_p\times\Delta^p}$$ is, as in the classical case, a map $$\nabla_p\colon \overline{\mathcal{E}_p} \to \overline{\mathcal{E}_p}\otimes_{\mathcal{O}_{Y^p}}\Omega^1_{Y_p\times\Delta^p}$$ such that the Leibnitz rule holds.
* **Definition.** Let $\nabla_\bullet$ be a collection of connections $(\nabla_p)_{p\in\mathbb{N}}$, where $\nabla_p$ is a connection on $\overline{\mathcal{E}_p}$. Consider, for all face maps $f_p^i$, the compositions
\begin{array}{ccccc}
    Y_p\times\Delta^{p-1} & \xrightarrow{\id\times f_p^i} & Y_p\times\Delta^p & \xrightarrow{\pi_p} & Y_p\\
    \downarrow \tiny{Y_\bullet f_p^i\times\id}\\
    Y_{p-1}\times\Delta^{p-1}\\
    \downarrow \tiny{\pi_{p-1}}\\
    Y_{p-1}
\end{array}
and the morphism $$\mathcal{E}_\bullet f_p^i\colon(Y_\bullet f_p^i)^*\mathcal{E}_{p-1} \to \mathcal{E}_p$$ of sheaves on $Y_p$. Then consider the induced morphism
\begin{equation*}
    (Y_\bullet f_p^i\times\id)^*\left(\overline{\mathcal{E}_{p-1}},\nabla_{p-1}\right) \to (id\times f_p^i)^*\left(\overline{\mathcal{E}_p},\nabla_p\right).
\end{equation*}
We say that $\nabla_\bullet$ is a **simplicial connection** (on $\mathcal{E}_\bullet$) if this morphism is flat.
